other_tests.procedure_name: CT ABD & PELVIS W & W/O CONTRAST, ADDL SECTIONS
other_tests.findings: The appendix, particularly distally is dilated up to 15 mm with moderate surrounding fat stranding. No associated organized fluid collection or evidence of macroscopic free air. Dependent atelectasis is mild. An 10-mm hypodense lesion in hepatic segment 8 is likely a cyst. No renal stones or focal renal masses. Mild fullness of the right renal pelvis compared to the left.
